@startuml
title User Command Execution (REST Polling Only)

actor User
participant "React Native App" as App
participant "REST Controller" as API
participant "Command Service" as Service
participant "MySQL (Commands)" as DB
participant "MQTT Broker" as Broker
participant "ESP32 Device" as Device

autonumber

== User Action ==

User -> App: Initiate Device Control (ON)
activate App

App -> API: POST /devices/{id}/on
activate API

API -> Service: createCommand(deviceId, action)
activate Service

Service -> DB: INSERT Command(status=CREATE)
activate DB
DB -->> Service: OK
deactivate DB

Service -> Broker: PUBLISH devices/{id}/control
note right
QoS 1
Payload: {commandId, action}
end note

Service -> DB: UPDATE status = SENT
DB -->> Service: OK

Service -->> API: 202 Accepted
deactivate Service

API -->> App: HTTP 202 Accepted
deactivate API


== Device Execution (Async MQTT) ==

Broker -> Device: Deliver control message
activate Device

Device -> Device: Execute action

alt Execution success
    Device -> Broker: PUBLISH response (SUCCESS)
else Execution failed
    Device -> Broker: PUBLISH response (FAILED)
end

deactivate Device


== Backend Response Handling ==

Broker -> Service: Deliver response
activate Service

Service -> DB: UPDATE status COMPLETED/FAILED
DB -->> Service: OK

deactivate Service


App -> App: Component re-render triggered
App -> API: GET /devices/{id}
API -> DB: SELECT device state
DB -->> API: Return updated device info
API -->> App: Return device data

App -> App: Update UI based on latest device state

@enduml
